The Senate will adjourn plenary today for a 19-day Easter break, it has been learnt. Senate President Ahmad Lawan announced this at the end of Wednesday’s plenary. He said the break would end on Tuesday, April 13, 2021. The Senate President explained that the Upper Chamber’s standing committees would continue to carry out their legislative functions during the period. “Our Committee on the Review of the 1999 Constitution, under the chairmanship of Deputy Senate President is working round the clock and so many other committees are working very hard. “So, this is just for the plenary to be closed. But, of course, our committees will continue to work. The Easter break will last from March 25 to April 13, 2021.”